{"title":"The conditional","body":[{"type":"p","text":"We use the conditional tense to refer to hypothetical situations. On the next page, this will be further explained."},{"type":"p","text":"The conditional tense works the same as the future tense, but instead of the present tense of the (irregular) verb zullen, we use the past tense:"},{"type":"table","table":[["ik","zou + infinitive","we","zouden + infinitive"],["je","zou + infinitive","jullie","zouden + infinitive"],["hij","zou + infinitive","ze","zouden + infinitive"]]},{"type":"table","table":[["zeggen","stem: zeg","luisteren","stem: luister"],["ik","zou zeggen","ik","zou luisteren"],["je","zou zeggen","je","zou luisteren"],["hij","zou zeggen","hij","zou luisteren"],["we","zouden zeggen","we","zouden luisteren"],["jullie","zouden zeggen","jullie","zouden luisteren"],["ze","zouden zeggen","ze","zouden luisteren"]]},{"type":"table","table":[["springen","stem: spring","betalen","stem: betaal"],["ik","zou springen","ik","zou betalen"],["je","zou springen","je","zou betalen"],["hij","zou springen","hij","zou betalen"],["we","zouden springen","we","zouden betalen"],["jullie","zouden springen","jullie","zouden betalen"],["ze","zouden springen","ze","zouden betalen"]]},{"type":"p","text":"A very useful web site is www.verbix.com."}]}